  "url": "https://www.ada.lk/breaking_news/\u0db6\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dbb-\u0d9c\u0dc4\u0dbd-\u0d85\u0db4\u0dd2\u0dc0-\u0db6\u0dba-\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1-\u0db6\u0dd0\u0dc4\u0dd0---\u0d85\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7-\u0d85\u0dc0\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dba-\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dba\u0da7-\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dc3\u0dca-\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda-\u0db1\u0dd1/11-396872",
  "time_ut": 1662271011,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db6\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dbb \u0d9c\u0dc4\u0dbd \u0d85\u0db4\u0dd2\u0dc0 \u0db6\u0dba \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db6\u0dd0\u0dc4\u0dd0 - \u0d85\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dc3\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda \u0db1\u0dd1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "We can't be scared by the eggs - the fighters won't change the way they want",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "All institutions under the Ministry of Urban Development and Housing will undergo a full audit. Urban Development and Housing Minister Mr. Prasanna Ranatunga instructed the Ministry Secretary today (4) to take the necessary steps for that.",
        "He pointed out that he has already received complaints about alleged irregularities in all the 21 institutions under his ministry during the previous government. The minister also said that he took this decision because he could not deal with the rubbish heaps of some former ministers.",
        "The Minister said this in a discussion held today (4) at the Urban Development Authority located in the first phase of Battaramulla, Setshiripaya.",
        "\u201cIf an organization is protected, its employees are protected. Therefore, we need to know how to stand up for our rights and protect the company we work for. During the previous government, the National Housing Development Authority has printed posters worth 137 million rupees.",
        "A court case is being heard in this regard. It's a waste. We can't even destroy the posters because of litigation. Those posters just rot. We are subjecting these institutions to a full audit to investigate such frauds, corruptions and irregularities. I do not destroy institutions or do things that harm the welfare of workers. But I cannot blame others for their sins.",
        "I don't need to say anything about the financial situation of the country. Many government institutions that are running at a loss have reached the point of closing down. Many people have lost their jobs. Under such circumstances, if the trade unions tighten their professional measures, who will cover the loss? I work amicably with trade unions. It appears instead. But I am not ready to work outside the law. They do not advocate for the safety of those who work like that.",
        "Building Materials Corporation is a for-profit entity. But if you work in the wrong way, this institution will also be destroyed. The employees of the Building Materials Corporation engaged in a 24-day strike for a woman's issue. They have joined the strike by reporting for duty. It was the ultimate mistake. An investigation was conducted under the leadership of a ministry secretary regarding the woman's issue. No one can challenge that. Let's discuss and solve the problems that have arisen in the institutions.",
        "It will be easier for all of us if the trade unions discuss and solve the problems before going on strike. Struggles without a leader have no existence. The true nature of the golf face struggle is now being revealed. The trade unions of an organization should not fall to that level. A trade union should take professional action according to a formal system. If not, the company they work for will lose.",
        "I came to rescue these institutions. I have appointed the highest qualified presidents who know the work to all these institutions. Give them your support. You can't scare us by threatening us. \"I am not ready to change as the strugglers want while doing politics,\" the minister added."
      ],
